<br>
I looked at the group members holding the Jail section it was a Monk, Cleric and Shawmen all 55-60.  The monk was tank and the Shawmen was slowing and casting endless chain's of DD spells.<br>
<br>
Now I fought in the Jail before, but I always felt I did more damage to the mob than I now understand I can really do on a whole.  I would cast my rain spells and was doing great I thought I was on a role and the mob's hp were dropping much faster than before.  I was gleaming because I felt useful.<br>
<br>
Wondering how much damage he was doing compared to me, I turned on the 'Other Hit's filter so I could see his damage. It about made me cry when I saw this tank dealing blows at the rate of 3 per second each dealing on average 70 damage to as high as 126 with out the 298 critical's he was getting.<br>
<br>
I must say I always thought our class was in need of some twinking and tinkering, however I saw the light for the fist time. He was doing 3x the amount of damage I was doing and had no limit on mana, the cleric who was him as well was telling me how much mana he had. All the time the shawmen was chain casting that spell that takes hp and gives him mana, providing a endless supply of DD spell damage.<br>
<br>
I knew monks were high damage, and rogue's too.  But it's this light that has just reinforced why I am in my last two months of EverQuest(see my post in the Rant Forum)<br>
<br>
To a end I can see our strengths in PBAOE groups, and on large raids with bane spells.  But how is one to get there?  VI hates us soloing and quadkiting(the immune mobs in SOL stands as a testament to this) and a nerf is just waiting to come out of the wood work on this one I feel.  VI has not done it yet only because we would raise such a (no better word for this so sorry guys) fit that our bitching is probably the only thing keeping us from tossing Glitter and Frosting at monsters in vain attempts to deal damage.<br>
<br>
With this I leave tonight as a very disappointed and disillusioned wizard, be well guys! <p><p align= "center"> <table width="290"><td style='filter: glow(color=yellow'
