<br>
As well, getting a clickable nuke item will help you greatly. Velks robe is a good example of that, you can always contribute decent damage regardless of how much mana you have. <br>
<br>
Another thing is mana. People still bitch but from where I'm sitting, the medding problem has been somewhat fixed (not completely, focus items ARE needed). With c3 readily available now, for groups and soloing (get one at the end of your raid, theri duration will last a full xp night sometimes) I med twice as fast as I did before. Mind you, 60 familiar/epic helps alot too.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 185<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/02 11:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's depressing</span><hr size=1> Aye, What a lot of wizards have been pointing out for a very long time.<br>
