<br>
I've been doing logs for my guild and I just don't see anything wrong.  <br>
<br>
Some interesting things I found when doing logs.<br>
<br>
Rains deal alot of damage!  <br>
Clarity 2 is our friend!<br>
Rogues and Monks indeed do alot of damage more so with discs and Rangers... YES, RANGERS are up there as well.  Paladins can take alot of damage.<br>
A 60 warrior will not outdamage a 60 wizard, more so with Clarity 2.  <br>
<br>
We can supply sustainable damage during regular groupings if we have C2 or any form of mana regen.  Without C2, we are as good as a melee wielding Fine Steel.<br>
<br>
As a class, the wizards are not gods but by no means are we useless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Need a log parsed?</span><br>  Posts: 655<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/02 12:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's depressing</span><hr size=1> In an experience group, it's all about mana regen for a wizard. I've all but proven than wizards need a boost to their sustainable damage output in order to be able to hold their own in an experience group (for those new to the research, here's the link: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.htm">home.attbi.com/~dmoen/wizdps.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ). It basically demonstrates that a wizard's sustainable damage output without a right click nuke lags behind all three of the melee specialists (rogue, monk, and warrior) at all levels. A wizard with a right click nuke does a bit better, eclipsing the warrior from 49-51, and again pre-60 when he/she acquires a Velk robe, but at 60, even with a Rend Robe (our best right click nuke) we lag behind the damage output of all 3 tanks, even warriors.<br>
<br>
Wizards do have the ability to dump mana to bring down selected foes quickly, and we have a few utility spells (snare, stun, root, evac) which give a bit more depth and utility to the wizard class. Some even claim that our sustained damage output should not reach that of even warriors, but I feel that claim is absurd. Currently, a wizard without a right click nuke does approximately half the damage of a well equipped rogue for most of his career (and for the middle ages of level 20-40 it's even worse).<br>
<br>
My proposal was to add more right click nukes and to reduce casting costs of DDs by 25% across the board. To see the effect that this simple change would have, see: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~dmoen/fixwiz.htm">home.attbi.com/~dmoen/fixwiz.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> . Wizards without items would track warriors fairly closely, while wizards with items would track monks pretty well (with rogues remaining the damage kings, which is as it should be).<br>
<br>
Verant has seen my research, and the proposal has been read by the live team. Unfortunately, balance is a difficult task, and even if wizards are fairly easy to balance, Verant would not want to put in a wizard fix without adressing mages, enchanters, and necromancers at the same time. Look at it this way: if Verant put in a patch that provided a substantial boost to Mage damage output without addressing Wizards, this board would erupt into constant flame wars. As the other classes have more utility, Verant really needs to answer the hard balance questions before they can provide even the simplest and most obvious fixes for Wizards.<br>
<br>
There will be a boost given to Wizards, but it will take time.<br>
<br>
